Sorry, I'll try to clarify what I mean.<br />I'm referring more to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zeno%27s_paradoxes" class="postlink">Zeno's paradox</a> which says in order to move something from point A to point B, it must first move to a point halfway between the two. And then halfway again, ad infinitum.<br /><br />So if I want to move on the x axis from point 0 to 100 at 0.5:<br />At frame 1: 50<br />Frame 2: 75<br />Frame 3: 87.5<br />Then: 93.75, 96.875, 98.4375... etc.<br />So at what step does the Canvas actually round-up to the next pixel?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1908">marcusbooster</a> — Tue May 03, 2011 3:10 pm</p><hr />
